==English==
===Etymology===
([[neologism]]) ''[[geek]]'' + ''-asm'' from [[orgasm]]

===Noun===
'''geekasm''' (Alternate spelling '''geekgasm''')
# (''[[slang]]'') Any extremely pleasurable feeling one experiences after seeing, or hearing, something particularly cool within the realm of information technology, or related fields that require intimate knowledge of complex systems.

==Reference== 
When they build a machine, if they do the calculations right, the machine works and you get this intense ... uhh ... just like a '''geekasm''', from knowing that what you created in your mind and on the computer is actually doing what you told it to do - ''MIT professor Alex Slocum, Scientific American Frontiers, May 21st 2002''

